    File        : GetAttributesForEnum
    Purpose     : Enum that controls if IRepositoryCacheTableFactory returns
                  attributes for Runtime or Design
    Syntax      :
    Description :
    Author(s)   : Mike Fechner / Consultingwerk Ltd.
    Created     : Wed May 25 20:22:28 CEST 2016
    Notes       :
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------*/

ROUTINE-LEVEL ON ERROR UNDO, THROW.

{Consultingwerk/products.i}

&IF DEFINED (NativeEnums) NE 0 &THEN
&GLOBAL-DEFINE CLASS ENUM
&ELSE
&GLOBAL-DEFINE CLASS CLASS
&ENDIF

USING Consultingwerk.*                                 FROM PROPATH .
USING Consultingwerk.Framework.Collections.*           FROM PROPATH .
USING Consultingwerk.SmartFramework.Repository.Class.* FROM PROPATH .
USING Progress.Lang.*                                  FROM PROPATH .

{&CLASS} Consultingwerk.SmartFramework.Repository.Class.GetAttributesForEnum
    &IF "{&CLASS}" EQ "CLASS" &THEN
    INHERITS Enum
    &ENDIF
        :

&IF "{&CLASS}" EQ "ENUM" &THEN
    DEFINE ENUM
&ENDIF

    {Consultingwerk/EnumMember.i DesignTime 0 GetAttributesForEnum}
    {Consultingwerk/EnumMember.i Runtime 1 GetAttributesForEnum}

&IF "{&CLASS}" EQ "ENUM" &THEN
    .
&ENDIF

&IF "{&CLASS}" EQ "CLASS" &THEN

    /*------------------------------------------------------------------------------
        Purpose: Constructor for the GetAttributesForEnum members
        Notes:
        @param piValue The internal (numeric) representation of the Enumeration member
        @param pcLabel The text label of the Enumaration member
    ------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
    CONSTRUCTOR PRIVATE GetAttributesForEnum (piValue AS INTEGER, pcLabel AS CHARACTER):
        SUPER ().

        ASSIGN THIS-OBJECT:Value = piValue
               THIS-OBJECT:Label = pcLabel .

    END CONSTRUCTOR.

    /*------------------------------------------------------------------------------
        Purpose: Returns a CharacterList with the names of the Enum members
        Notes:
        @return The CharacterList with the names of the Enum members
    ------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
    METHOD PUBLIC STATIC CharacterList GetNames ():

        RETURN NEW CharacterList ('{&EnumMembers}':U).

    END METHOD .

    {Consultingwerk/EnumFromString.i Consultingwerk.SmartFramework.Repository.Class.GetAttributesForEnum}

&ENDIF

END {&CLASS} .
